SIMPLE: offspring
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Offspring
<hw>Off"spring`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. sing. & pl.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Off</ets> + <ets>spring</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of production; generation.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is produced; a child or children; a
descendant or descendants, however remote from the stock.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To the gods alone⟦br⟧
Our future <qex>offspring</qex> and our wives are known.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Origin; lineage; family.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Fairfax.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>off-street</ent>⟦br⟧
